scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: Second Guard
line: There's Dolabella sent from Caesar; call him.

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: First Guard
line: What work is here! Charmian, is this well done?

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: CHARMIAN
line: It is well done, and fitting for a princess

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: CHARMIAN
line: Descended of so many royal kings.

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: CHARMIAN
line: Ah, soldier!

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: DOLABELLA
line: How goes it here?

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: Second Guard
line: All dead.

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: DOLABELLA
line: Caesar, thy thoughts

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: DOLABELLA
line: Touch their effects in this: thyself art coming

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: DOLABELLA
line: To see perform'd the dreaded act which thou

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: DOLABELLA
line: So sought'st to hinder.

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: DOLABELLA
line: O sir, you are too sure an augurer;

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: DOLABELLA
line: That you did fear is done.

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: OCTAVIUS CAESAR
line: Bravest at the last,

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: OCTAVIUS CAESAR
line: She levell'd at our purposes, and, being royal,

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: OCTAVIUS CAESAR
line: Took her own way. The manner of their deaths?

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: OCTAVIUS CAESAR
line: I do not see them bleed.

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: DOLABELLA
line: Who was last with them?

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: First Guard
line: A simple countryman, that brought her figs:

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: First Guard
line: This was his basket.

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: OCTAVIUS CAESAR
line: Poison'd, then.

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: First Guard
line: O Caesar,

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: First Guard
line: This Charmian lived but now; she stood and spake:

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: First Guard
line: I found her trimming up the diadem

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: First Guard
line: On her dead mistress; tremblingly she stood

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: First Guard
line: And on the sudden dropp'd.

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: OCTAVIUS CAESAR
line: O noble weakness!

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: OCTAVIUS CAESAR
line: If they had swallow'd poison, 'twould appear

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: OCTAVIUS CAESAR
line: By external swelling: but she looks like sleep,

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: OCTAVIUS CAESAR
line: As she would catch another Antony

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: OCTAVIUS CAESAR
line: In her strong toil of grace.

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: DOLABELLA
line: Here, on her breast,

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: DOLABELLA
line: There is a vent of blood and something blown:

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: DOLABELLA
line: The like is on her arm.

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: First Guard
line: This is an aspic's trail: and these fig-leaves

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: First Guard
line: Have slime upon them, such as the aspic leaves

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: First Guard
line: Upon the caves of Nile.

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: OCTAVIUS CAESAR
line: Most probable

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: OCTAVIUS CAESAR
line: That so she died; for her physician tells me

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: OCTAVIUS CAESAR
line: She hath pursued conclusions infinite

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: OCTAVIUS CAESAR
line: Of easy ways to die. Take up her bed;

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: OCTAVIUS CAESAR
line: And bear her women from the monument:

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: OCTAVIUS CAESAR
line: She shall be buried by her Antony:

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: OCTAVIUS CAESAR
line: No grave upon the earth shall clip in it

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: OCTAVIUS CAESAR
line: A pair so famous. High events as these

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: OCTAVIUS CAESAR
line: Strike those that make them; and their story is

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: OCTAVIUS CAESAR
line: No less in pity than his glory which

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: OCTAVIUS CAESAR
line: Brought them to be lamented. Our army shall

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: OCTAVIUS CAESAR
line: In solemn show attend this funeral;

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: OCTAVIUS CAESAR
line: And then to Rome. Come, Dolabella, see

scene: SCENE II.  Alexandria. A room in the monument.
speaker: OCTAVIUS CAESAR
line: High order in this great solemnity.
